{# templates/symfony-x/welcome.html.twig #}
{% extends 'symfony-x/website.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Symfony-X{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
    <h1 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl"><span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r to-emerald-600 from-sky-400">Welcome to</span> Symfony-X</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
        Symfony-X is a Symfony LAST Stack rapid project development and deployment environment for the purpose of creating a minimal viable product in minimal viable time.
    </p>
    <br />
    <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
        If you know what you're doing, take this Symfony setup and run with it. If you're new, use the Symfony-X default setup as a reference to learn how to build a LAST Stack Symfony project. The default setup provided is segragated into its own directories, usually named `symfony-x`. You may wish to review `importmap.php` as well as `assets/controllers/` to customize any javascript libraries and controllers.
    </p>
    <br />
    <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
